n.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Award Winning disabled poet Lynn Manning performing at Noche de Poetas (Poetry Night): Disability Poetics, Bodies, Language and the Word, at the Latino Cultural Center. Manning's work challenges the intersections of race and disability. Originally a visual artist he became blind at the age of 23 and began painting with words.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Disabled poet Maria Palacios, from the Disability Arts Performance organization Sins Invalid, performs one of her poems.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Disabled dancer Ginger Lane, a member of Momenta Dance Company, performs an integrated dance piece with a partner.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Disabled poet, dancer and activist Pennie Brinson at one of her poetry readings.               Space    Back to main content           Bodies of Work Exhibit                  UIC Logo        Disability Cultural Center       Contact   Disability Cultural Center  1007 W. Harrison St., 235 BSB, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 355-7050  dcc@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Instagram            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  Â© 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 